			<h2 class="section">FORMS<a name="forms">&nbsp;</a></h2>

		  <h3 class="firstsection">Region 1 Forms</h3>
		  <p><strong>NOTE:</strong> You will need Adobe Acrobat Reader (<a href="https://www.adobe.com/">free download</a>) to view PDF files.</p>
		  <ul>
			<li><a href="../../documents/monitoring/forms/SoLoSDM_Form_080909.xls">SoLo Soil Disturbance Monitoring Form (SDM - blank form)</a> (Excel file - 413 KB) and associated <a href="../../documents/monitoring/forms/SoLoSDM_Form_ReadMeFirst_Sept_2008.pdf">"Read Me First" file</a> (PDF - 21 KB) <br /><span class="dateupdated">[Document added to this page on 05/19/2008; most recently updated on 09-11-2008]</span> <br /><br />   The latest version of the electronic spreadsheet with the file name
   "SoLoSDM_Form_080909.xls" has the following changes from previous versions: <br /><br />

   An option has been added (row 2, column BG, in the Data Entry worksheet)
   to allow the user to choose either a 10% (&plusmn; 5%) overall confidence
   interval width or a 20% width (&plusmn; 10% of the estimate).  Previous
   versions only had a 10% overall interval width.  The default is set for
   the narrower interval, and changing this width to 20% should be
   considered with caution.  We recommend only making this change with
   direction from the line officer.  The result of choosing the wider
   interval is such that little information is actually known about the
   estimate, particularly in the case of low disturbance levels (for
   example, a 20% interval around an estimated 10% disturbance gives an
   interval estimate between 0% and 20% which does not provide specific
   enough information to know whether the standards are being met or not). <br /><br />

   The calculation for the lower confidence bound has been set to
   automatically truncate the interval at 0 in cases where the disturbance
   is low enough to result in a negative value.  Previous versions required
   the user to truncate manually.

</li>
      </ul>
      
